benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Retrieve account tags

covered: Valid Request: Multiple happy-path scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06) verify successful retrieval and combinations of query parameters.
Empty Response: TC06 verifies behavior when an account has no tags (empty JSON array).
Query Parameters: Good coverage of includeDeleted and audit options, including valid combinations and invalid audit value (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC09).

Input Validation: Many input validation edge-cases for accountId are covered (invalid format, partial UUID, empty, whitespace) (TC08, TC20, TC21, TC22) and protection against injection/XSS (TC14, TC15).
Error Scenarios: 4xx handling for invalid accountId (400) and not-found account (404) are present (TC07, TC08); downstream error handling is included (TC24).
Authorization: Missing and invalid auth token scenarios are present (TC12, TC13), verifying 401 handling.
Performance/Scale: Large result set and concurrency/performance scenarios are present (TC16, TC17).
Regression/Compatibility: Regression and backward compatibility scenarios are included (TC18, TC19).
Integration/Data Consistency: Integration and downstream consistency tests are present (TC24, TC25).
gaps: Pagination: No tests exercise pagination parameters or behavior (page, limit, offsets) despite the presence of large datasets; pagination behavior, limits and boundary conditions are not validated.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios validate caching headers (ETag, Last-Modified, Cache-Control) or conditional GET behavior (304 responses).
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No tests verify behavior under rate limits or excessive requests (429 responses), beyond concurrency/performance timing checks.
Authorization Scope/Permissions: Tests cover missing/invalid tokens (401) but do not cover insufficient permissions (403) or role-based access variations.

Response Schema Validation: While presence of Tag objects is asserted, there are no explicit tests asserting full schema correctness for Tag objects (required fields, types, presence/absence depending on audit level) beyond audit presence.
Pagination + Performance Interaction: Although a large dataset test exists, it doesn’t validate paginated retrieval or the server behavior when returning subsets of data (sorting, stable ordering).
Caching + Conditional Requests: No tests for conditional GET (If-None-Match / If-Modified-Since) to verify 304 responses and ETag semantics.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: include scenarios that exercise page/limit/offset parameters, validate correct slicing, boundary conditions (page size 0, max page size), and behavior when requesting beyond available pages.
Add caching/conditional-get tests: assert presence and correctness of ETag and Cache-Control headers; include conditional GET tests (If-None-Match / If-Modified-Since) to expect 304 when appropriate.
Add rate-limiting tests: simulate burst requests to validate 429 handling and backoff behavior; combine with concurrency tests to exercise throttling policies.
Expand authorization tests: add tests for insufficient privileges/roles expecting 403, and test token expiration and scopes if applicable.
Add strict schema validation: verify each Tag object fields and types, and ensure audit-level differences (NONE/MINIMAL/FULL) match expected fields and content.
Pagination + performance: combine large dataset with pagination to validate performance and stable ordering across pages.
Add security-negative tests around headers and response content (e.g., verify no sensitive headers are leaked), and validate consistent error message formats and codes across error scenarios.
